<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-04T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-04T18:00:00-05:00" n="200" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/10660</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-04T23:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 4, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 5, 10.16
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5714. War Trade Board [from <persName>Stetson</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>No. 566. Referring Department’s 5937, October 17, your No. 383.<note n="1" xml:id="d200fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1069">p.
                                        1069</ref>.</note> We are advised by His Britannic Majesty’s
                                delegate, Paris, that (1) British Government will not make a more
                                definite reply to Spanish note protesting against the black lists
                                than that already made, (2) it is therefore not necessary to ask you
                                to say anything to the Spanish Government at the moment, and (3)
                                that the matter can be dropped unless further action is taken by the
                                Spanish Government. We would appreciate being kept informed when any
                                protest is received by you and, if so, what answer you make.
                                    <persName>Stetson</persName>.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>